creator: madhu.sudan@xansa.com
knst.kolinko@gmail.com
text:
The archive you are trying to unpack is not ZIP, it is a Tar+GZIP bundle.

1. Try to rename the extension of the downloaded file from '.tar.gz' 
into '.tgz' before calling WinZIP.

2. The JAR utility from JDK is for ZIP archives, not for Tar+GZIP bundles, it 
cannot process this format of files.

3. If (1.) did not help, try to rename the extension into '.tar'. I have seen 
some times, that Internet Explorer have automatically applied GZIP unpacking to 
such files, so that they became plain TARs.
